1
00:00:00,720 --> 00:00:02,230
Dragon Slayer's Secret Art!

2
00:00:04,250 --> 00:00:06,980
Has she already mastered them both?!

3
00:00:07,360 --> 00:00:08,300
There it is!

4
00:00:08,300 --> 00:00:09,440
Go!

5
00:00:09,440 --> 00:00:11,500
Wendy knows the Secret Art?!

6
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:13,000
Incredible!

7
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:14,200
She's as good as won.

8
00:00:15,300 --> 00:00:16,850
What is this?

9
00:00:16,850 --> 00:00:18,140
A magic wind barrier?

10
00:00:19,260 --> 00:00:20,560
You've sealed us inside!

11
00:00:21,490 --> 00:00:23,980
Light Burst: Sky Drill!

12
00:00:37,960 --> 00:00:39,100
Cheria!

13
00:00:39,100 --> 00:00:41,520
Yeah!

14
00:00:39,700 --> 00:00:41,230
She did it!

15
00:00:45,720 --> 00:00:48,530
I haven't mastered Milky Way yet...

16
00:00:49,560 --> 00:00:51,860
...so this was my full force.

17
00:00:53,530 --> 00:00:54,780
I used all my magic...

18
00:00:55,320 --> 00:00:57,430
W-Well, well...

19
00:01:00,550 --> 00:01:03,170
You were wonderful, Wendy.

20
00:01:06,320 --> 00:01:08,040
Maybe I went overboard...

21
00:01:08,650 --> 00:01:09,900
But this way...

22
00:01:10,760 --> 00:01:12,600
Cheria's down!

23
00:01:12,600 --> 00:01:16,170
The winner, from Fairy Tail A...

24
00:01:16,170 --> 00:01:18,850
Sorry! Wait a second!

25
00:01:19,150 --> 00:01:20,990
I'm just getting started!

26
00:01:23,270 --> 00:01:27,020
You're impressive, Wendy.

27
00:01:28,550 --> 00:01:31,420
Are you okay? Want to give up?

28
00:03:02,470 --> 00:03:08,280
Aye, sir! The Grand Magic Games 
are really picking up steam!

29
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:10,690
Natsu's Fairy Tail Team A

30
00:03:10,690 --> 00:03:14,900
was in eighth place for the qualifier, 
barely making it to the real games,

31
00:03:14,900 --> 00:03:16,970
and then they got creamed the first day.

32
00:03:16,970 --> 00:03:19,500
But even so, through Natsu's good showing,

33
00:03:19,500 --> 00:03:22,220
their points rose little by little!

34
00:03:22,220 --> 00:03:25,840
But with Raven Tail's pesky obstructions...

35
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:28,810
...B Team got off to a rocky start, too.

36
00:03:29,750 --> 00:03:32,890
And we can't forget Sabertooth.

37
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:36,320
Currently, they're known as 
the strongest guild in Fiore.

38
00:03:36,880 --> 00:03:40,780
They've got two Dragon Slayers 
in their ranks, Sting and Rogue.

39
00:03:40,990 --> 00:03:43,170
Their abilities are top-notch.

40
00:03:43,170 --> 00:03:46,830
A lot happened with Yukino, 
a Celestial Spirit Wizard,

41
00:03:46,830 --> 00:03:48,890
but they're formidable enemies.

42
00:03:49,830 --> 00:03:53,550
Speaking of "a lot happened", 
Raven Tail's Alexei

43
00:03:53,550 --> 00:03:56,000
was revealed to be guild master Ivan!

44
00:03:56,000 --> 00:04:00,030
Ivan is our master Makarov's son.

45
00:04:00,030 --> 00:04:02,830
In other words, he's Laxus's son.

46
00:04:02,830 --> 00:04:08,260
And Gajeel had been working as a double 
agent in order to investigate Raven Tail.

47
00:04:08,260 --> 00:04:11,980
At last, the showdown between 
father and son guilds was over.

48
00:04:12,230 --> 00:04:16,650
Continuing with the battle 
part, Wendy was up next

49
00:04:16,650 --> 00:04:18,840
against Cheria from Lamia Scale!

50
00:04:18,840 --> 00:04:20,630
She's Sherry's cousin!

51
00:04:20,890 --> 00:04:28,800
I hear Lamia Scale and Blue Pegasus once 
allied with Fairy Tail to battle Oracion Seis?

52
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:30,440
That's right!

53
00:04:30,440 --> 00:04:34,850
A magical celebration with a mix 
of old faces and new guilds,

54
00:04:34,850 --> 00:04:36,460
that's the Grand Magic Games!

55
00:04:36,460 --> 00:04:39,830
Alright, everyone! Thank 
you for your patience!

56
00:04:39,830 --> 00:04:42,840
Let's continue with the 
Wendy vs. Cheria battle!

57
00:04:42,840 --> 00:04:46,800
Hooray! Hooray! Fairy Tail!

58
00:04:58,630 --> 00:05:01,280
I guess you're not going to give up?

59
00:05:04,830 --> 00:05:06,000
Wendy!

60
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:07,510
She can barely stand!

61
00:05:08,330 --> 00:05:09,260
Wendy...

62
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:11,540
This is an incredible fight...

63
00:05:18,930 --> 00:05:20,620
Small Fist!

64
00:05:25,750 --> 00:05:27,950
If that Cheria girl

65
00:05:27,950 --> 00:05:30,010
has some connection to Zeref...

66
00:05:33,220 --> 00:05:35,120
...Wendy is in danger!

67
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:36,230
Hey, you!

68
00:05:36,580 --> 00:05:37,980
Huh? This guy...

69
00:05:38,220 --> 00:05:39,350
From Fairy Tail...?

70
00:05:39,940 --> 00:05:42,750
Should I stop this? Or wait and see?

71
00:05:45,810 --> 00:05:46,780
Wendy...

72
00:05:48,590 --> 00:05:50,360
But right now...

73
00:05:51,550 --> 00:05:54,850
Seven years ago, I infiltrated Fairy Tail.

74
00:05:56,270 --> 00:06:00,150
To some extent, I'm acquainted with 
inside information on Fairy Tail.

75
00:06:01,380 --> 00:06:02,250
Mystogan...

76
00:06:02,950 --> 00:06:05,490
You're not supposed to exist in this world.

77
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:19,420
I don't mind fighting,

78
00:06:19,420 --> 00:06:23,940
but I've got no love for one-sided 
violence where the outcome is clear.

79
00:06:29,440 --> 00:06:32,570
The Council... At a time like this...

80
00:06:33,170 --> 00:06:36,130
You know, you can always surrender.

81
00:06:38,860 --> 00:06:39,920
I can't!

82
00:06:47,290 --> 00:06:50,770
The fact that I'm standing here

83
00:06:50,770 --> 00:06:54,770
means that I'm prepared 
to fight for my guild!

84
00:06:55,330 --> 00:06:56,810
I don't need your pity.

85
00:06:57,220 --> 00:06:59,880
Until I fall and can't move anymore,

86
00:06:59,880 --> 00:07:01,600
come at me with everything you've got!

87
00:07:01,850 --> 00:07:02,940
Please!

88
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:07,360
Wendy...

89
00:07:16,960 --> 00:07:18,280
Sure.

90
00:07:18,280 --> 00:07:19,870
That's only common courtesy.

91
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:21,120
Right!

92
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:24,620
Well, now it's my turn 
to break out a big move!

93
00:07:26,050 --> 00:07:28,990
I'll make it easy on you and 
end this with one strike.

94
00:07:33,970 --> 00:07:35,510
God Slayer's Secret Art!

95
00:07:35,510 --> 00:07:36,820
Cheria, no!

96
00:07:36,820 --> 00:07:37,960
Not that!

97
00:07:38,280 --> 00:07:41,350
Fool! Do you mean to kill your opponent?!

98
00:07:45,450 --> 00:07:48,440
I'm answering the full strength of 
your feelings with my full strength!

99
00:07:48,440 --> 00:07:50,530
That's what love is!

100
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:57,870
W-What is that magic?!

101
00:07:58,700 --> 00:07:59,620
That's...

102
00:07:59,910 --> 00:08:02,780
Heaven's Gathering Clouds!

103
00:08:16,260 --> 00:08:17,290
She dodged it!

104
00:08:17,690 --> 00:08:19,510
No... It missed her!

105
00:08:20,140 --> 00:08:23,570
It seems Cheria can heal 
herself with her magic,

106
00:08:23,570 --> 00:08:25,660
but it only works on wounds.

107
00:08:25,660 --> 00:08:28,040
It looks like she can't 
recharge herself with energy.

108
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:29,220
Right.

109
00:08:29,770 --> 00:08:33,660
Wendy's the opposite. She can't 
heal herself with her magic,

110
00:08:33,660 --> 00:08:35,800
but she can restore another 
person's strength.

111
00:08:35,800 --> 00:08:37,230
I see...

112
00:08:38,290 --> 00:08:39,660
Then...

113
00:08:39,660 --> 00:08:42,790
...she revived her opponent's 
physical strength?!

114
00:08:45,250 --> 00:08:49,130
And because of that, Cheria's 
magic gained too much force...

115
00:08:54,390 --> 00:08:55,880
Wendy made her miss...

116
00:08:56,180 --> 00:08:58,760
...by increasing her strength!

117
00:09:03,040 --> 00:09:04,850
What strategy!

118
00:09:04,850 --> 00:09:06,140
Amazing!

119
00:09:06,440 --> 00:09:07,710
Crushing Fang...

120
00:09:08,670 --> 00:09:10,130
...of the Sky Dragon!

121
00:09:11,780 --> 00:09:14,110
That's great, Wendy!

122
00:09:28,170 --> 00:09:31,310
This is an incredible turn of events!

123
00:09:31,310 --> 00:09:33,700
Neither side is giving any ground!

124
00:09:33,700 --> 00:09:38,550
It's a clash of little fists! Is this 
tenacity for the sake of their guilds?!

125
00:09:41,330 --> 00:09:42,410
I can't stop this...

126
00:09:47,060 --> 00:09:49,120
Though their fists are small,

127
00:09:50,160 --> 00:09:52,580
their passion is vast...

128
00:10:01,770 --> 00:10:04,240
Go! Neither of you lose!

129
00:10:07,730 --> 00:10:08,710
Wendy...

130
00:10:24,540 --> 00:10:25,650
And so...

131
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:28,840
...time has run out!

132
00:10:41,660 --> 00:10:46,370
The match is over and it's a draw!

133
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:52,400
Both teams receive five points!

134
00:10:52,400 --> 00:10:53,820
Awesome!

135
00:10:53,820 --> 00:10:56,130
You did great, Wendy!

136
00:10:56,130 --> 00:10:57,830
Both of them were magnificent.

137
00:10:58,300 --> 00:10:59,340
Yep.

138
00:10:59,750 --> 00:11:02,160
Cheria and Wendy both did very well.

139
00:11:02,160 --> 00:11:03,850
We were lucky to get to see that.

140
00:11:05,930 --> 00:11:09,930
This is the best match I've seen yet!

141
00:11:10,510 --> 00:11:15,280
Even though judging them on magic 
alone, Cheria's level is far higher...

142
00:11:15,820 --> 00:11:17,270
U-Um...

143
00:11:17,800 --> 00:11:18,900
I...

144
00:11:19,300 --> 00:11:22,000
I'm no good when it comes to battle,

145
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:26,630
but I can use a lot of support magic 
that'll be useful to everyone.

146
00:11:26,630 --> 00:11:31,330
So... So please don't leave me out!

147
00:11:31,960 --> 00:11:33,920
The girl from back then...

148
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:37,010
...has grown this much...

149
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:39,770
Wendy...

150
00:11:39,770 --> 00:11:42,090
W-What are you crying for?

151
00:11:49,850 --> 00:11:52,270
Did it hurt? I'm sorry.

152
00:11:52,270 --> 00:11:54,690
I'm fine. That's all I hear from you.

153
00:11:58,880 --> 00:12:01,100
That was fun, Wendy.

154
00:12:04,690 --> 00:12:05,740
My wounds...

155
00:12:06,780 --> 00:12:09,620
I enjoyed it too, a little.

156
00:12:09,830 --> 00:12:12,600
Hey, let's be friends, okay?

157
00:12:13,470 --> 00:12:14,240
Sure.

158
00:12:14,240 --> 00:12:16,030
I mean, if you want me as a friend...

159
00:12:16,030 --> 00:12:17,350
No, no, no!

160
00:12:17,350 --> 00:12:18,840
Answer like friends are supposed to.

161
00:12:21,500 --> 00:12:23,840
Let's be friends, Wendy!

162
00:12:25,350 --> 00:12:26,980
Sure, Cheria!

163
00:12:30,580 --> 00:12:33,180
What a moving ending!

164
00:12:33,180 --> 00:12:37,060
For this old man, the tournament is over!

165
00:12:37,060 --> 00:12:40,410
Hold on there. Just the third day is over.

166
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:44,230
Thank you, everyone!

167
00:12:53,630 --> 00:12:54,410
What's this?!

168
00:12:55,330 --> 00:12:59,450
Even though the fight's over, that 
sinister magic is still around?!

169
00:13:00,260 --> 00:13:03,320
Then Cheria isn't the source of that magic?!

170
00:13:05,700 --> 00:13:06,590
It's from over there!

171
00:13:07,250 --> 00:13:08,540
Heading towards the exit!

172
00:13:15,070 --> 00:13:16,030
Did he notice me?

173
00:13:17,180 --> 00:13:18,170
But...

174
00:13:25,670 --> 00:13:28,200
And so, the third day ended.

175
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:33,020
At this point, Sabertooth is 
the top team with 34 points.

176
00:13:33,020 --> 00:13:35,330
Mermaid Heel is in second place.

177
00:13:35,330 --> 00:13:37,420
Lamia Scale is in third,

178
00:13:37,420 --> 00:13:39,750
making those the best three.

179
00:13:39,750 --> 00:13:42,990
Below them, the order goes Fairy Tail B, A,

180
00:13:42,990 --> 00:13:45,260
and then Blue Pegasus.

181
00:13:45,770 --> 00:13:49,280
Fairy Tail's showing is unexpected.

182
00:13:49,610 --> 00:13:54,060
Perhaps I need to think a bit-k-kabo...

183
00:13:58,820 --> 00:14:00,860
The source of that mysterious magic...

184
00:14:03,770 --> 00:14:05,320
It's him!

185
00:14:06,070 --> 00:14:07,270
I found him!

186
00:14:15,060 --> 00:14:16,080
He came out of nowhere!

187
00:14:16,320 --> 00:14:17,510
You're not going anywhere.

188
00:14:21,090 --> 00:14:24,290
Even though the person who possesses that 
mysterious magic is right over there...

189
00:14:25,150 --> 00:14:26,800
Who are you?!

190
00:14:27,220 --> 00:14:29,050
I'll put him to sleep.

191
00:14:29,510 --> 00:14:30,550
No...

192
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:34,560
Right now, I'm supposed 
to be a Fairy Tail wizard.

193
00:14:35,010 --> 00:14:37,380
I can't lay a hand on a 
member of the Council.

194
00:14:38,590 --> 00:14:41,230
Doranbolt, what's all the commotion about?

195
00:14:41,530 --> 00:14:42,210
Dammit!

196
00:14:42,680 --> 00:14:45,580
I know you're not Mystogan.

197
00:14:46,140 --> 00:14:47,110
So who are you?

198
00:15:09,400 --> 00:15:10,840
I'll ask once more.

199
00:15:11,290 --> 00:15:12,590
Who are you?!

200
00:15:13,780 --> 00:15:16,310
Sorry. I'm in a hurry.

201
00:15:17,170 --> 00:15:18,560
Oh, no, you don't!

202
00:15:19,100 --> 00:15:21,520
Mystogan isn't in Earthland.

203
00:15:21,520 --> 00:15:23,270
I'm Mystogan.

204
00:15:24,520 --> 00:15:25,650
What are you...?!

205
00:15:26,900 --> 00:15:28,400
Who are you?!

206
00:15:35,510 --> 00:15:37,400
I'm starvin'!

207
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:38,940
Come on, Natsu!

208
00:15:38,940 --> 00:15:42,370
I'm trying to bask in the afterglow 
of that touching ending!

209
00:15:42,370 --> 00:15:45,050
I can't help bein' hungry!

210
00:15:45,050 --> 00:15:48,370
Alright, let's get somethin' to eat, Happy!

211
00:15:48,800 --> 00:15:50,690
He's incorrigible...

212
00:15:51,420 --> 00:15:53,300
M-Me too...

213
00:15:53,300 --> 00:15:55,260
Aye, sir!

214
00:15:55,260 --> 00:15:56,800
Yeesh...

215
00:15:56,800 --> 00:15:57,930
Ah, well...

216
00:15:58,200 --> 00:16:01,100
We got to see a good match today.

217
00:16:01,100 --> 00:16:03,170
I'm sure dinner will be really good tonight.

218
00:16:05,400 --> 00:16:06,900
Crap...

219
00:16:11,620 --> 00:16:12,990
Jellal?!

220
00:16:34,840 --> 00:16:40,110
Oh, so there you are, Mystogan-kun!

221
00:16:40,350 --> 00:16:41,470
Yajima-san!

222
00:16:42,770 --> 00:16:44,250
Lahar-kun...

223
00:16:44,250 --> 00:16:48,620
You can understand why Mystogan-kun 
hides his face, can't you?

224
00:16:49,270 --> 00:16:54,110
He was unlucky enough to be born 
with the same face as Jellal.

225
00:16:54,450 --> 00:16:56,850
I hope you understand.

226
00:16:56,850 --> 00:16:58,740
You're saying... He's another person?!

227
00:16:59,540 --> 00:17:03,080
Perhaps you know of the world called Edolas?

228
00:17:03,080 --> 00:17:05,680
Yes. I heard about it from 
one of my subordinates.

229
00:17:06,060 --> 00:17:09,730
That world and this one are connected.

230
00:17:09,730 --> 00:17:12,920
There are people who have the same faces.

231
00:17:13,810 --> 00:17:16,800
Then you're from Edolas?

232
00:17:17,510 --> 00:17:18,170
Yeah.

233
00:17:18,840 --> 00:17:21,280
That was a great match, wasn't it?!

234
00:17:20,620 --> 00:17:21,810
Yep!

235
00:17:27,850 --> 00:17:29,300
Jellal!

236
00:17:31,570 --> 00:17:32,660
Kagura!

237
00:17:35,410 --> 00:17:37,110
Hey, what's wrong?!

238
00:17:37,110 --> 00:17:37,900
Kagura-san!

239
00:17:37,900 --> 00:17:38,700
Kagura-chan!

240
00:17:46,620 --> 00:17:48,420
Kagura! Get a hold of yourself!

241
00:17:48,900 --> 00:17:51,190
Somebody call for a medic!

242
00:17:51,190 --> 00:17:52,360
Kagura-chan is...

243
00:17:52,360 --> 00:17:53,290
What's wrong?!

244
00:17:53,290 --> 00:17:54,710
Is she okay?

245
00:17:58,460 --> 00:17:59,610
Jell...

246
00:18:04,120 --> 00:18:06,730
I'm all right now. I've calmed down.

247
00:18:07,140 --> 00:18:09,170
But <i>he's</i> over there...

248
00:18:10,080 --> 00:18:11,280
I know.

249
00:18:12,030 --> 00:18:13,440
I'm okay now.

250
00:18:13,830 --> 00:18:14,780
I'm sorry.

251
00:18:17,800 --> 00:18:19,950
So they've been hiding him...

252
00:18:21,650 --> 00:18:23,810
Jellal in Fairy Tail...?

253
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:27,030
Why, Er-chan?!

254
00:18:31,420 --> 00:18:33,790
I appreciate your understanding.

255
00:18:33,790 --> 00:18:34,850
Oh, no.

256
00:18:34,850 --> 00:18:38,180
I apologize for not knowing 
the circumstances.

257
00:18:39,520 --> 00:18:42,920
To me, Jellal is an evil being.

258
00:18:43,350 --> 00:18:45,510
If I run into him, you 
can bet I'll report him.

259
00:18:45,910 --> 00:18:46,650
Good.

260
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:47,860
Well then...

261
00:18:48,790 --> 00:18:51,450
I owe you, Yajima-san.

262
00:18:51,450 --> 00:18:53,490
Just this once.

263
00:18:53,490 --> 00:18:56,980
Get out of here before you 
cause Makarov any trouble.

264
00:18:56,980 --> 00:18:57,730
Yes.

265
00:18:58,450 --> 00:19:01,250
I swear I'll be gone by the 
time the tournament is over.

266
00:19:04,250 --> 00:19:05,750
That was the real thing.

267
00:19:07,330 --> 00:19:09,930
I don't want Yajima-san to lose face here,

268
00:19:09,930 --> 00:19:11,350
but we won't let <i>him</i> get away!

269
00:19:22,480 --> 00:19:23,960
Did I lose him?

270
00:19:25,240 --> 00:19:28,520
That magic was like Zeref's 
and yet it wasn't his.

271
00:19:29,600 --> 00:19:30,980
Who are you?!

272
00:19:54,520 --> 00:19:55,500
Maybe...

273
00:19:56,380 --> 00:20:01,450
...somewhere in Gramps' 
heart, he had faith in you.

274
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:04,380
Because you're father and son...

275
00:20:05,340 --> 00:20:07,890
Silence!

276
00:20:09,810 --> 00:20:13,580
I've been waiting all this time for this day!

277
00:20:13,580 --> 00:20:17,400
It was all to get Lumen Histoire!

278
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:20,820
Where is Lumen Histoire?! Where is it?!

279
00:20:20,820 --> 00:20:25,950
Tell me, Laxus! You're my son, aren't you?!

280
00:20:30,490 --> 00:20:31,450
Gramps...

281
00:20:32,220 --> 00:20:34,470
What's Lumen Histoire?

282
00:20:36,660 --> 00:20:38,750
You heard this from Ivan?

283
00:20:39,620 --> 00:20:44,170
Heard about it? All I know 
is he wanted it badly.

284
00:20:44,560 --> 00:20:47,610
That brat will be the end of me...

285
00:20:48,960 --> 00:20:51,890
He called it "Fairy Tail's darkness".

286
00:20:57,420 --> 00:20:59,110
It's not darkness.

287
00:20:59,110 --> 00:21:00,430
First Master!

288
00:21:02,350 --> 00:21:04,140
Lumen Histoire...

289
00:21:04,700 --> 00:21:07,490
That's our guild's light.

290
00:21:07,490 --> 00:21:09,950
First Master, you mustn't!

291
00:21:10,610 --> 00:21:11,860
I know.

292
00:21:11,860 --> 00:21:16,200
Only the master of this guild 
has the right to know about it.

293
00:21:17,930 --> 00:21:20,880
Laxus, do you understand?

294
00:21:21,400 --> 00:21:24,420
If it ain't anything weird, then 
I won't bother looking into it.

295
00:21:24,990 --> 00:21:26,760
Thank you!

296
00:21:27,150 --> 00:21:32,270
But where did Ivan get 
ahold of that information?

297
00:21:33,540 --> 00:21:34,770
The second master...

298
00:21:35,730 --> 00:21:37,190
It was likely Purehito.

299
00:21:39,480 --> 00:21:41,690
It's possible...

300
00:21:42,490 --> 00:21:45,210
I never imagined that Purehito 
would fall to the dark side.

301
00:21:46,170 --> 00:21:48,740
And now, as a result of my 
shallow-brained selection...

302
00:21:48,740 --> 00:21:50,080
No.

303
00:21:50,080 --> 00:21:52,290
It's not your fault, First Master.

304
00:21:52,540 --> 00:21:54,190
It is my fault!

305
00:21:55,110 --> 00:21:56,250
I...

306
00:22:03,270 --> 00:22:05,670
First Master!

307
00:22:07,090 --> 00:22:10,480
G-Gramps! What do we do?!

308
00:22:10,480 --> 00:22:13,810
I'm not crying! Not at all!

309
00:22:14,080 --> 00:22:17,730
I'm not... crying...

310
00:22:18,560 --> 00:22:20,100
Laxus!

311
00:22:20,100 --> 00:22:22,730
Go on, hold her!

312
00:22:22,730 --> 00:22:24,900
That hurdle's too high!

313
00:23:55,650 --> 00:23:58,450
Hey, hey, another battle in bathing suits!

314
00:23:58,450 --> 00:23:59,560
Say, Natsu!

315
00:23:59,560 --> 00:24:03,860
Just before, I saw a swimsuit that was laid 
out in the dressing room of another guild.

316
00:24:03,860 --> 00:24:04,390
Yeah, so?

317
00:24:04,390 --> 00:24:06,300
It was just the bottoms!

318
00:24:06,300 --> 00:24:08,630
Meaning a contestant went out there topless!

319
00:24:08,630 --> 00:24:10,870
Huh! That's wild!

320
00:24:10,870 --> 00:24:13,990
That's not really the reaction 
I was looking for...

321
00:24:13,990 --> 00:24:16,510
Next time: Naval Battle!

322
00:24:16,510 --> 00:24:17,960
What kind of reaction did you expect?

323
00:24:17,960 --> 00:24:20,140
"Wowie! Are you serious?!" Like that...

324
00:24:20,140 --> 00:24:23,520
Or "I'm goin' to the front line!"

325
00:24:23,520 --> 00:24:24,480
What the hell is that?

